Title: MAD-FINAL-OCRI 
Project Persona: Foodie Traveler
Name: Tony Stark (The Foodie Traveler)
Age: 30
Occupation: Travel Blogger / Culinary Enthusiast
Personality: Adventurous, Social, Detail-Oriented

Background: 
- Tony Stark is a culinary adventurer who loves to explore and experience the best dining spots worldwide. With a fast-paced lifestyle, 
Tony values efficiency, innovation, and cutting-edge technology in travel and food discovery. He enjoys discovering hidden gems, 
curated recommendations, and sharing his experiences with a community of food lovers.

Pain Points & Challenges: 
- Hates wasting time on unreliable reviews and scattered information
- Prefers a personalized experience over generic restaurant listings
- Struggles to find trusted, reservation-friendly places on the go
- Expects a sleek, intuitive app that matches his high standards

App Fit & Key Features: 
- Restaurant Discovery: DiscoverScreen for exploring food spots globally
- Review System: ReviewsScreen for user-generated reviews and ratings 
- Admin Controls: AdminScreen for managing content and user experiences
- Profile Management: ProfileScreen for personal preferences and logout option


Ideal User Journey in the App: 
- Tony signs up or logs in lands on DiscoverScreen
- Browses recommended restaurants with images, ratings, and details
- Reads user reviews on ReviewsScreen for deeper insights
- Shares a review after dining and engages with other travelers



 Roles & Responsibilities

Ocampo,Franchesca ( Designer ) 
  -Task: Upload design files (e.g., header & nav design) and create issues.
  Workflow: 
    - Create a branch for design updates.
    - Upload design assets (e.g., PSD, JPEG, or design mockup files) or update design-related code (HTML/CSS).
    - Create a PR for review.
    - Revise designs based on feedback from the combined Documenter/QA.

 Rivadenra, Kenneth ( Documenter/QA )
  -Task: Create Markdown documentation (e.g., plans, design decisions) and manage quality assurance by reviewing PRs, posting issues, and providing feedback.
  Workflow: 
    - Create and update documentation files (e.g., `plan.md`, `design-decisions.md`) on a dedicated branch.
    - Push changes and open a PR tagging all members.
    - Review PRs submitted by Designer or Devs.
    - Post issues or add comments to request improvements and revisions.
    - Ensure documentation reflects the latest project changes and decisions.

Bayor, Jhimmar ( Devs ) 
  - Task: Implement code changes, push commits, and manage PRs.
  Workflow:  
    - Create a feature branch from the main branch to work on assigned issues.
    - Code the required changes (implement design or functionality).
    - Push commits to GitHub and open a PR tagging the Documenter/QA.
    - Revise code based on feedback or comments.
    - Merge changes once approved, ensuring the branch stays updated with QA-approved modifications.
    




